Check node disk usage
df -h
Physical Storage Locations on Node

Ephemeral storage typically resides in the following directories on a node:

/var/lib/containerd
/var/lib/docker
/var/lib/kubelet
/var/log/pods

These directories contain:

Container writable layers

Container logs

Pod temporary data

emptyDir volumes

Ephemeral Storage vs Persistent Storage
Feature	Ephemeral Storage	Persistent Storage
Lifetime	Pod lifetime	Independent of Pod
Data persistence	Lost when Pod stops	Data retained
Storage location	Node local disk	External storage
Example	emptyDir	PVC / PV

Examples of persistent storage:

AWS EBS

NFS

Ceph

Azure Disk

