Common Interview Questions
1. What happens when ephemeral storage is full?

Kubernetes detects DiskPressure on the node and begins evicting pods to free space.

2. What is the difference between ephemeral storage and emptyDir?
Feature	Ephemeral Storage	emptyDir
Type	Temporary node storage	Volume type
Scope	Container writable layer, logs, volumes	Shared pod volume
Lifecycle	Pod lifetime	Pod lifetime
3. Where is ephemeral storage located?

Ephemeral storage resides on the node's local disk.

Typical paths include:

/var/lib/containerd
/var/lib/docker
/var/log/pods
/var/lib/kubelet
Simple Definition

Ephemeral storage is temporary node-local storage used by containers for writable layers, logs, and temporary volumes, and it is deleted when the pod terminates.
